'''"No shit, Sherlock"''' was a common expression in the [[1990s|90s]] referring to dialogue between the characters [[Doctor Watson]] and [[Sherlock Holmes|Sherlock]] in Sir [[Arthur Conan Doyle]]'s mystery series, [[Sherlock Holmes]].  In the novels and stories, Watson would frequently be told to dig up dirt on a crime suspect.  The phrase "No shit, Sherlock" would be spoken by Watson to report to the detective that he had not discovered any incriminating evidence, although he never said this in print.  The statement is usually jokingly directed at someone who makes an utterly obvious statement, by sarcastically attributing the name of a detective who makes brilliant deductions. The reality is that they showed not only minimal intelligence but also stupidity. A somewhat common retort is "Keep looking Watson".

